<eesti> Ekspordihinna ja normaalv&auml;&auml;rtuse vahel tehakse &otilde;iglane v&otilde;rdlus. </eesti>
<inglise> This comparison shall be made at the same level of trade and in respect of sales made at as nearly as possible the same time, which will normally mean sales within three months before or after the sale under investigation, or in the absence of such sales, any appropriate period. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealune v&otilde;rdlus tehakse samal kaubandustasandil ning v&otilde;imalikult &uuml;hel ja samal ajal toimunud m&uuml;&uuml;kide p&otilde;hjal, tavaliselt kolme kuu jooksul enne v&otilde;i p&auml;rast uuritavat m&uuml;&uuml;ki toimunud m&uuml;&uuml;ke, v&otilde;i selliste m&uuml;&uuml;kide puudumise korral muu sobiva ajavahemiku jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> Due allowance shall be made in each case, on its merits, for differences which affect price comparability, including differences in conditions and terms of sale, contractual penalties, taxation, level of trade, quantities, physical characteristics, and any other differences which are also demonstrated to affect price comparability. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga juhtumi puhul v&otilde;etakse n&otilde;uetekohaselt eraldi arvesse hinna v&otilde;rreldavust m&otilde;jutavad erisused, kaasa arvatud need, mis on seotud m&uuml;&uuml;gitingimuste ja -t&auml;htaegadega, leppetrahvidega, maksustamisega, kaubandustasandiga, kogustega, f&uuml;&uuml;siliste omadustega, ning k&otilde;ik muud erisused, mis samuti v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada hinna v&otilde;rreldavust. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, in cases referred to in paragraph 10, price comparability has been affected, the normal value shall be established at a level of trade equivalent to the level of trade of the constructed export price, or due allowance made, as warranted, under this paragraph. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui l&otilde;ikes 10 nimetatud juhtudel on hinna v&otilde;rreldavust m&otilde;jutatud, siis m&auml;&auml;ratakse normaalv&auml;&auml;rtus kindlaks arvestusliku ekspordihinna kaubandustasandiga v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsel kaubandustasandil v&otilde;i tehakse n&otilde;uetekohane korrigeerimine k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Any duplication when making adjustments shall be avoided, in particular in relation to discounts and contractual penalties. </inglise>
<eesti> Korrigeerimisel v&auml;lditakse dubleerimist, eelk&otilde;ige seoses allahindluste ja leppetrahvidega. </eesti>
<inglise> When the price comparison requires a conversion of currencies, such conversion shall be made using the rate of exchange on the date of sale, except that when a sale of foreign currency on forward markets is directly linked to the export sale involved, the rate of exchange in the forward sale shall be used. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui hinnav&otilde;rdlus n&otilde;uab valuuta konverteerimist, siis kasutatakse konverteerimisel m&uuml;&uuml;gi kuup&auml;eva konverteerimiskurssi, v.a juhul, kui v&auml;lisvaluuta m&uuml;&uuml;k ennakturgudel on vahetult seotud asjaomase eksportm&uuml;&uuml;giga, siis kasutatakse t&auml;htp&auml;evam&uuml;&uuml;gi kurssi. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this provision, the date of sale shall be the date on which the material terms of sale are established, normally the date of contract. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva s&auml;tte kohaldamisel loetakse m&uuml;&uuml;gikuup&auml;evaks oluliste m&uuml;&uuml;gitingimuste kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise kuup&auml;ev, mis tavaliselt on lepingu allakirjutamise kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise> However, if the material terms of sale are significantly changed on another date, the rate of exchange on the date of the change should be applied. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui olulistes m&uuml;&uuml;gitingimustes tehakse m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rseid muudatusi, siis tuleks kasutada muudatuste tegemise kuup&auml;eval kehtivat konverteerimiskurssi. </eesti>
<inglise> In such case, appropriate adjustments shall be made to take into account any unreasonable effect on the injurious pricing margin due solely to exchange rate fluctuations between the original date of sale and the date of this change. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellisel juhul tehakse vajalikud korrigeerimised, et k&otilde;rvaldada igasugune ebaratsionaalne toime kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaalile, mis tuleneb &uuml;ksnes konverteerimiskursi k&otilde;ikumistest esialgse m&uuml;&uuml;gikuup&auml;eva ja k&otilde;nealuse muudatuse tegemise kuup&auml;eva vahel. </eesti>
<inglise> D. Injurious pricing margin </inglise>
<eesti> D. K a h j u s t a v a h i n n a k u j u n d u s e m a r g i n a a l </eesti>
<inglise> 12. </inglise>
<eesti> 12. </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to the relevant provisions governing fair comparison, the existence of injurious pricing margins shall normally be established on the basis of a comparison of a weighted average normal value with a weighted average of prices of all sales, or by a comparison of individual normal values and individual export prices on a transaction-to-transaction basis. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &otilde;iglast v&otilde;rdlust reguleerivatest asjakohastest s&auml;tetest ei tulene teisiti, siis m&auml;&auml;ratakse kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaalide olemasolu tavaliselt kindlaks kaalutud keskmise normaalv&auml;&auml;rtuse ja k&otilde;igi m&uuml;&uuml;gitehingute hindade kaalutud keskmise v&otilde;rdlemise alusel v&otilde;i &uuml;ksiknormaalv&auml;&auml;rtuste ja &uuml;ksikekspordihindade v&otilde;rdlemise alusel tehingult tehingule p&otilde;him&otilde;ttel. </eesti>
<inglise> However, a normal value established on a weighted average basis may be compared to prices of all individual sales, if there is a pattern of export prices which differ significantly among different purchasers, regions or time periods, and if the methods specified in the first sentence of this paragraph would not reflect the full degree of injurious pricing being practised. </inglise>
<eesti> Kaalutud keskmise p&otilde;hjal m&auml;&auml;ratud normaalv&auml;&auml;rtust v&otilde;ib siiski v&otilde;rrelda k&otilde;igi &uuml;ksikm&uuml;&uuml;kide hindadega, kui ekspordihindade struktuuris esinevad olulised erinevused seoses eri ostjate, piirkondade v&otilde;i ajavahemikega ning kui k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike esimeses lauses m&auml;rgitud meetodid ei kajasta t&auml;iel m&auml;&auml;ral kasutatava kahjustava hinnakujunduse tegelikku astet. </eesti>
<inglise> 13. </inglise>
<eesti> 13. </eesti>
<inglise> The injurious pricing margin shall be the amount by which the normal value exceeds the export price. </inglise>
<eesti> Kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaal on summa, mille v&otilde;rra normaalv&auml;&auml;rtus &uuml;letab ekspordihinna. </eesti>
<inglise> Where injurious pricing margins vary, a weighted average injurious pricing margin may be established. </inglise>
<eesti> Varieeruvate kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaalide puhul v&otilde;ib kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata kaalutud keskmise kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaali. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Determination of injury </inglise>
<eesti> Kahju kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Pursuant to this Regulation, the term 'injury' shall, unless otherwise specified, be taken to mean material injury to the Community industry, threat of material injury to the Community industry or material retardation of the establishment of such an industry and shall be interpreted in accordance with the provisions of this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ei ole kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud teisiti, siis t&auml;hendab m&otilde;iste "kahju" k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusele tekitatud olulist kahju, &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusele olulise kahju tekitamise ohtu v&otilde;i &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusharu rajamise olulist pidurdamist ning seda t&otilde;lgendatakse k&auml;esolevas artiklis etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> A determination of injury shall be based on positive evidence and shall involve an objective examination of both (a) the effect of the sale at less than normal value on prices in the Community market for like vessels, and (b) the consequent impact of that sale on the Community industry. </inglise>
<eesti> Kahju m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks kindlate t&otilde;endite alusel ning selle juurde kuulub ka objektiivne uurimine, mis h&otilde;lmab a) normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest v&auml;iksemate hindadega m&uuml;&uuml;gi m&otilde;ju samalaadsete laevade hindadele &uuml;heduse turul ning b) k&otilde;nealusest m&uuml;&uuml;gist tulenevat m&otilde;ju &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusele. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> With regard to the effect of the sale at less than normal value on prices, consideration shall be given to whether there has been significant price undercutting by the sale at less than normal value as compared with the price of like vessels of the Community industry, or whether the effect of such sale is otherwise to depress prices to a significant degree or prevent price increases which would otherwise have occurred, to a significant degree. </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest v&auml;iksemate hindadega m&uuml;&uuml;gi toimega hindadele tuleb kaaluda, kas alla normaalv&auml;&auml;rtust m&uuml;&uuml;gi puhul on esinenud olulist hinna allal&ouml;&ouml;mist v&otilde;rreldes &uuml;heduse t&ouml;&ouml;stuse samalaadsete laevade hinnaga v&otilde;i kas selline m&uuml;&uuml;k on muul viisil m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt m&otilde;jutanud hindade allal&ouml;&ouml;mist v&otilde;i on olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral takistanud hinnat&otilde;use, mis vastasel juhul oleks toimunud. </eesti>
<inglise> No one or more of these factors can necessarily give decisive guidance. </inglise>
<eesti> Tingimata otsustava t&auml;htsusega ei ole ei &uuml;ks ega mitu k&otilde;nealustest teguritest. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Where sales of vessels from more than one country are simultaneously subject to injurious pricing investigations, the effects of such sales shall be cumulatively assessed only if it is determined that (a) the margin of injurious pricing established in relation to the purchases from each country is more than de minimis as defined in Article 7 (3) and that (b) a cumulative assessment of the effects of the sales is appropriate in the light of the conditions of competition between vessels sold by non-Community shipbuilders to the buyer and the conditions of competition between such vessels and the like Community vessels. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui seoses kahjustava hinnakujundusega uuritakse samal ajal rohkem kui &uuml;he riigi laevade m&uuml;&uuml;ki, siis v&otilde;ib selliste m&uuml;&uuml;kide toimet kumulatiivselt hinnata ainult juhul, kui tehakse kindlaks, et a) iga riigi ostudega seotud kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaal on suurem kui artikli 7 l&otilde;ikes 3 m&auml;&auml;ratletud miinimumtase ja b) kui m&uuml;&uuml;gi toime kumulatiivne hindamine on vajalik, v&otilde;ttes arvesse muude kui &uuml;hendusse kuuluvate laevaehitajate poolt ostjale m&uuml;&uuml;dud laevade vahelisi konkurentsitingimusi ning selliste laevade ja samalaadsete &uuml;henduse laevade vahelisi konkurentsitingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The examination of the impact of the sale at less than normal value on the Community industry concerned shall include an evaluation of all relevant economic factors and indices having a bearing on the state of the industry including: the fact that an industry is still in the process of recovering from the effects of past dumping, injurious pricing or subsidization, the magnitude of the actual margin of injurious pricing, actual and potential decline in sales, profits, output, market share, productivity, return on investments, utilization of capacity; factors affecting Community prices; actual and potential negative effects on cash flow, inventories, employment, wages, growth, ability to raise capital or investments. </inglise>
<eesti> Uurides normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;gi toimet asjaomasele &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusharule, antakse hinnang k&otilde;igile asjakohastele majandusteguritele ja n&auml;itajatele, mis m&otilde;jutavad t&ouml;&ouml;stuse seisundit, kaasa arvatud: asjaolu, et t&ouml;&ouml;stusharu on toibumas varasema dumpingu, kahjustava hinnakujunduse v&otilde;i subsideerimise m&otilde;judest, kahjustava hinnakujunduse marginaali tegelik ulatus, m&uuml;&uuml;gi, kasumi, toodangu, turuosa, tootlikkuse, investeeringutasuvuse, tootmisv&otilde;imsuse tegelik ja v&otilde;imalik v&auml;henemine; &uuml;henduse hindu m&otilde;jutavad tegurid; tegelik ja v&otilde;imalik negatiivne m&otilde;ju rahavoole, varudele, t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivel, palkadele, kasvule, kapitali v&otilde;i investeeringute suurendamise v&otilde;imalustele. </eesti>
<inglise> This list is not exhaustive, nor can any one or more of these factors necessarily give decisive guidance. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev loetelu ei ole ammendav ning tingimata otsustava t&auml;htsusega ei ole ei &uuml;ks ega mitu k&otilde;nealust tegurit. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> It must be demonstrated, from all the relevant evidence presented in relation to paragraph 2, that the sale at less than normal value is causing, or has caused, injury within the meaning of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;igi l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt esitatud asjaomaste t&otilde;endite varal peab selguma, et normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;k tekitab v&otilde;i on tekitanud kahju k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Specifically, this shall entail a demonstration that the price levels identified pursuant to paragraph 3 are responsible for an impact on the Community industry as provided for in paragraph 5, and that this impact exists to a degree which enables it to be classified as material. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige t&auml;hendab see t&otilde;endamist, et l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt kindlaks tehtud hinnad p&otilde;hjustavad l&otilde;ikes 5 k&auml;sitletud m&otilde;ju &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusele ning k&otilde;nealuse m&otilde;ju ulatus on nii suur, et seda tuleb pidada oluliseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> Known factors other than the sale at less than normal value which at the same time are injuring the Community industry shall also be examined to ensure that injury caused by these other factors is not attributed to the sale at less than normal value under paragraph 6. </inglise>
<eesti> Peale normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;gi tuleb uurida ka teisi tuntud tegureid, mis samal ajal tekitavad kahju &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stusele, tagamaks, et k&otilde;nealuste muude tegurite p&otilde;hjustatud kahju ei arvataks normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;gist tuleneva kahju hulka l&otilde;ike 6 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Factors which may be considered in this respect include the volume and prices of sales by shipbuilders of countries other than the exporting country not realized at less than normal value, contraction in demand or changes in the patterns of consumption, restrictive trade practices of, and competition between, third country and Community producers, developments in technology and the export performance and productivity of the Community industry. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellega seoses v&otilde;ib arvesse v&otilde;tta j&auml;rgmisi tegureid: muude kui ekspordimaa laevaehitajate m&uuml;&uuml;gimaht ja -hinnad, kui m&uuml;&uuml;k ei toimu normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga, n&otilde;udluse langemine ning tarbimisharjumuste muutumine, kolmanda riigi ja &uuml;henduse tootjate piiravad kaubandustavad ning nendevaheline konkurents, tehnika areng ning &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stuse ekspordisuutlikkus ja tootlikkus. </eesti>
<inglise> 8. </inglise>
<eesti> 8. </eesti>
<inglise> The effect of the sale at less than normal value shall be assessed in relation to the production of the Community industry of like vessels when available data permit the separate identification of that production on the basis of such criteria as the production process, producers' sales and profits. </inglise>
<eesti> Normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;gi toimet hinnatakse &uuml;henduse samalaadsete laevade toodanguga v&otilde;rreldes, kui kasutamiseks k&auml;ttesaadavad andmed v&otilde;imaldavad k&otilde;nealust toodangut identifitseerida niisuguste kriteeriumide alusel nagu tootmisprotsess, m&uuml;&uuml;k ja kasum. </eesti>
<inglise> If such separate identification of that production is not possible, the effects of the sale at less than normal value shall be assessed by examination of the production of the narrowest group or range of vessels, which includes the like vessel, for which the necessary information can be provided. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&otilde;nealust toodangut ei ole v&otilde;imalik eraldi identifitseerida, siis hinnatakse normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;ki, v&otilde;rreldes seda k&otilde;ige v&auml;iksema samalaadset laeva sisaldava laevar&uuml;hma toodanguga, mille kohta on v&otilde;imalik saada vajalikku infot. </eesti>
<inglise> 9. </inglise>
<eesti> 9. </eesti>
<inglise> A determination of a threat of material injury shall be based on facts and not merely on allegation, conjecture or remote possibility. </inglise>
<eesti> Olulise kahju tekitamise ohu kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisel tuginetakse faktidele, mitte vihjetele, oletustele ega kaudsetele v&otilde;imalustele. </eesti>
<inglise> The change in circumstances which would create a situation in which the sale at less than normal value would cause injury must be clearly foreseen and imminent. </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaolude muutumine, mis v&otilde;ib esile kutsuda olukorra, mille puhul normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;k tekitab kahju, peab olema selgesti prognoositav l&auml;hituleviku kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> In making a determination regarding the existence of a threat of material injury, consideration should be given to, inter alia, such factors as: </inglise>
<eesti> Olulise kahju tekkimise ohu kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisel tuleks muu hulgas arvesse v&otilde;tta j&auml;rgmisi tegureid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) sufficient freely disposable capacity of the shipbuilder or an imminent and substantial increase in such capacity indicating the likelihood of substantially increased sales at less than normal value, account being taken of the availability of other export markets to absorb any additional exports; and </inglise>
<eesti> a) laevaehitaja vabalt kasutatav piisav tootmisv&otilde;imsus v&otilde;i sellise v&otilde;imsuse oluline kasv l&auml;hiajal, mis osutab v&otilde;imalikule m&auml;rgatavalt suuremale m&uuml;&uuml;gile normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga, kusjuures tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta muude eksporditurgude suutlikkust tarbida igasugust t&auml;iendavat eksporti; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) whether vessels are being exported at prices that would, to a significant degree, depress prices or prevent price increases which otherwise would have occurred, and would probably increase demand for further purchases from other countries. </inglise>
<eesti> b) laevade eksport hindadega, mis v&otilde;iksid olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral hindu alandada v&otilde;i takistada hinnat&otilde;use, mis vastasel juhul oleksid tekkinud, ning t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt suurendavad n&otilde;udlust edasiste ostude j&auml;rele teistest riikidest. </eesti>
<inglise> No one of the factors listed above by itself can necessarily give decisive guidance, but the totality of the factors considered must lead to the conclusion that further sales at less than normal value are imminent and that, unless protective action is taken, material injury will occur. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski loetletud teguritest ei ole &uuml;ksikuna tingimata otsustava t&auml;htsusega, kuid k&otilde;ik vaadeldavad tegurid koos sunnivad j&auml;reldama, et normaalv&auml;&auml;rtusest madalama hinnaga m&uuml;&uuml;k ohustab vahetult ning tekitab olulist kahju, kui kaitsemeetmeid ei v&otilde;eta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Definition of Community industry </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stuse m&auml;&auml;ratlemine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation, the term 'Community industry' shall be interpreted as referring to the Community producers as a whole capable of producing a like vessel with their present facilities or whose facilities can be adapted in a timely manner to produce a like vessel, or to those of them whose collective capability to produce a like vessel constitutes a major proportion, as defined in Article 5 (6), of the total Community capability to produce a like vessel. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses t&auml;hendab &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stus &uuml;henduse tootjaid kui tervikut, kuhu kuuluvad tootjad, kes olemasolevate seadmetega on v&otilde;imelised ehitama samalaadse laeva v&otilde;i suudavad seadmed &otilde;igel ajal kohandada samalaadse laeva ehitamiseks, v&otilde;i seda osa laevaehitajatest, kelle &uuml;hine suutlikkus ehitada samalaadne laev moodustab artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 6 m&auml;&auml;ratluse kohaselt olulise osa &uuml;henduse samalaadse laeva ehitamise kogusuutlikkusest. </eesti>
<inglise> However, when producers are related to the shipbuilder, exporters or buyers or are themselves buyers of the allegedly injuriously priced vessel, the term 'the Community industry' may be interpreted as referring to the rest of the producers. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tootjad on seotud laevaehitaja, eksportija v&otilde;i ostjaga v&otilde;i kui nad ise on v&auml;idetavalt kahjustava hinnakujundusega laeva ostjad, siis v&otilde;ib m&otilde;istet "&uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stus" t&otilde;lgendada &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud tootjaid h&otilde;lmavana. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of paragraph 1, producers shall be considered to be related to the shipbuilder, exporters or buyers only if (a) one of them directly or indirectly controls the other; or (b) both of them are directly or indirectly controlled by a third person; or (c) together they directly or indirectly control a third person, provided that there are grounds for believing or suspecting that the effect of the relationship is such as to cause the producer concerned to behave differently from non-related producers. </inglise>
